reviewText: Shipping was a little slow I guess from the size. Great product.
Very light construction with cool air flow.  Great for those hot summer days.

I've only worn this for a few weeks, but it's definitely a keeper.  The material is thin, polished, basket-woven paper straw which has a soft flexibility and is actually quite tough and water-resistant.  The comfortable elasticized headband holds it securely even with the headband tucked inside, which is how I wear it in all but the windiest conditions.  My headsize is 22-1/4 inches or 56.5 cm diameter, and there is room for someone with a larger headsize, perhaps an inch or more.  The brim is adjustable, and there is a wire sewn into the edge so you can flatten or increase the roll.  Along with the light weight, I most like this hat for its venting, which is very effective.

Another reviewer seems put off by the fact that this is a product made from paper.  I have produced handmade papers in several workshops over the years.  I  can assure you that many fibrous materials are used to make all kinds of paper, and some of them are extremely strong ... stronger, even, than natural straw.

UPDATE 2017: Four years since I bought this hat, and it has held up amazingly well.  Been used on warm spring days as I cut brush and do other yard work. Nice wide brim spares me the inconvenience of wearing sun blocker.
summary: Vented outback hat is comfortable and cool

reviewText:
I am constantly working on improving my Wonder Woman costume, so I ditched the gold cloth band and picked these up.

I love how sturdy they are and how you can just squeeze to adjust - though I almost wish they would cinch just a bit more so I could wear them properly at the wrist.

Probably my biggest problem with them was that they produced a green stain on my arms when I wore my costume to Comic Con. Fortunately, it was easy to wash off, but Wonder Woman is not green like Gamorra! (I've been told a quick fix would be to coat with clear nail polish.)

For the price, these are fantastic bangles and PERFECT for a Wonder Woman costume. I would recommend doing the coating thing BEFORE wearing for long periods, just to avoid those green wrists!

Brought to you by:
*C.S. Light*
summary: Works great for Wonder Woman costume, minus the green wrists.

Understanding that these are meant to be snug fitting PJs, we ordered the size 7-8 for our above average height 5 year old, and the fit is perfect for her.  We generally order up to be sure that the length is ok for her, especially with the top.  It fits her a bit loose, but snug enough - and most importanly, long enough to cover her mid section when she moves around!  Definitely size up when ordering.  We love the print - but are unfortunately not as pleased with the quality of the fabric.  There are generally two ways to make garments with prints -- one where the fibers are woven of different colors to make up the print, and the other where the fibers are woven of one color with a print applied to the finished product.  This PJ is the latter - wherein the print looks great until you actually wear it and it stretches, and then the print becomes distorted because the knit rows pull apart and show the plain white knit of the fabric in the middle of the print.  Anywhere that the PJs bend at all - think bottom, knees, elbows -- ends up looking worn out and faded just because of the way the print is applied to the cotton knit.  But, other than this, our daughter loves them -- they are comfortable for her, and she loves the print.  She doesn't notice how bad it ends up looking after she wears them for awhile.  Other than this issue with the fabric/ print, the quality of the product is just fine.  The cotton is not super thick, which is actually good for our daughter.  Overall, the product is fine - especially for the relatively low price tag. However, we would not order from this manufacturer again.
summary: cute print, order a size up or two if your child is average/ above average height or weight for age

reviewText: These orthotics were amazing for me. They were recommended by my foot doctor. I have a lot of pain in my foot because of flat feet and severe arthritis.  But since wearing these I'm able to stand and walk so much better than before.
I wear these inserts to help with plantar fasciitis and high arches.

These are great for someone that needs large arch support

I love the full length Powerstep orthotics.  For the 3/4 length, I was disappointed that Amazon did not have the women's size 7 - 8.5 as I order a fair amount of other things on Amazaon, and had to order these elsewhere.  I have received them from another source, and will comment that the front edge could be a little thinner for a more comfortable feel and transition beneath the ball of the foot. I measured that thickness to be about 1/8" or 3.5 mm.  The height of the arch support reaches just over 1" without a foot in it.  Length measured from the middle is 6 3/4" front to back, widest part of heel cup area measures 2.5."  The Birkenstock 3/4 length orthotics are thinner at the front edge, so there is a better transition there.  But they are more expensive than Powerstep.  The Powerstep insoles have the leather on top, which creates a very comfortable feel.  They seem to be quite sturdy.  They work well with a 1/2" to 3/4" heel lift that I have to wear in one shoe, and that is with a low-heeled dress sandal, no built-in orthotic support, with a "gladiator" type of heel back (no ties) to keep the orthotics in place without adding adhesive or velcro.  With other sandals, I have yet to find an adequate adhesive solution to keep these orthotics (or any type of orthotics) in place while, of course, walking around on them.
summary: A little thick at the front edge

Wonderful product. It is well made. Only a couple of drawbacks, but they are minor and to be expected with a costume... 1. The gloves have cloth 'claws' that you slide your fingertips into. They don't stay on your fingers well and are not easy to tuck into the gloves. (I solved this dilemma by simply cutting them off with a pair of scissors.) 2. The hood is a little long in the back; this causes it to almost cover my eyes (which I don't really mind). I will sometimes tuck the back seam under the collar of my coat if I don't want it in my face or I'll tuck it under and safety-pin it. I'm planning on fixing the arc of the seam myself with my sewing machine, but for those less handy with a needle and thread, either safety-pins or an alteration might be needed...unless you have a longer neck than I do. ^-^ 3. Both the skirt and the top are a little revealing-leggings and an undershirt might be needed.  Other than that, I love this costume! The leg warmers are wonderfully warm, the fur is soft and the seams are well stitched. Even with the minor problems, I would definitely recommend this product!

Long story short: horrible build quality with loose threads and cardboard behind the eyes, smells like a high school science class on dissection day no matter how many times you wash it.  (And I had to clean out the washer and dryer to get rid of the smell from *there*.)  I just got an overwhelming feeling that *wearing* it would be hazardous to my health.

I'd recommend spending the extra money to buy a normal kigu from Sazac.  Not being able to wear them in the summer is better than not being able to wear them at all.

Bought the black leggings with white dots for a Halloween costume, and was happy with the result.
Sizing warning: I'm currently a US size 6 or 8 and would not have been able to wear these leggings were I any larger in the hips/waist.

Positives:
The white dots are not painted on; they're part of the fabric, so they won't split or fade over time.
They are not super see-through (though if you want to try to wear them in lieu of pants I'd caution you to test the outfit in bright light before heading out).

Neutrals:
They're a synthetic fabric, so they're not as warm and comfy as cotton leggings. (And which means I'll rarely wear them now that Halloween is over.)
The fact that the dots don't line up at the front seam (as I knew from the product picture) means I will only wear them under a skirt or dress.

I would recommend this coat if you are looking for rain gear and not fashion.

My kiddo is REALLY into those snug-fitting cotton pajamas that have video game and superhero characters on them. He is also quite tall for his age, and slender, and because of his 6'3" Dad, grows like a weed.  Imagine our dismay when at age 8, he has outgrown all of the cool superhero PJs because they don't make them past a size 10, anywhere. I searched all over and these were what I managed to find. Luckily, there are some decent designs he liked, so we ordered three pair.

They fit just as well and are even more soft and snuggly than the superhero ones, and though they are sadly void of superheroes, they do the trick, and he is really happy with them. I am so glad we were at least able to find a reasonably-priced, cotton substitute that still fits his tall thin frame and wraps him in snuggly comfort. If you're like me and don't want your kid wrapped in toxic chemical flame-retardants that can cause cancer and who knows what else, these might be the PJs for you.

As long as you know this bag is designed to hold only the essentials you will love it.  My 13 inch MacBook Pro fits perfectly.  It holds my iPad, charger, mouse, phone and keys with no problem.  BUT that is about it.  If you want a small but durable bag for these things you won't be disappointed.  I have had it for a few days so i can't speak about durability yet but the materials seem to be good quality.

The laptop pocket fit my Dell XPS12 easily and I appreciate that it has a separate padded pocket for my tablet.  I was specifically looking for a bag without a lot of bulk as I like to travel light.  It has lots of pockets: one on the flap, one zip up pocket and 3 open pockets under the flap (2 of which are padded), and a pocket on the back.  That being said, other than the pocket for the laptop itself all the other pockets are very flat and won't hold a lot of bulky items.  If you're looking for a laptop bag that can carry around a few other items this is a great bag.  If you're looking for a bag that can carry everything plus a laptop then this won't do to the job.

My only real concern is that the plastic buckles on the front of the bag and the strap feel very flimsy.  I can see that they would wear down and possibly even break with a lot of rough use.  I also wish it had side pockets for things like water bottles or an umbrella, but like I said, this isn't a bag that holds everything.  I bought it specifically to carry my work laptop between home and the office so I think it'll be fine for that application but I'm not sure it would stand up to lots of heavy use.
summary: Nice for the price, but doesn't feel sturdy

reviewText:
I've been wearing these shades since 1989 when I starting spending a lot of time at FL35 looking out the 34" window in the side of our airplane.  My then girlfriend recommended them to me, and I really thought it was all about a good commission check for her, because at the time, I had never spent more than $10 on a pair of sunglasses.  I was always losing them somewhere.  I had that pair for 9 years when they got stolen.  I bought them again at a pretty significant price increase.
I forgot them on a trip one time, and bought a pair of Maui Jim shades in New Orleans at a Sunglass Hut.  They assured me they would be just as good.  They weren't even in the same ballpark.  Not bad shades if your goal is looking good, but they were useless for blocking bright sunlight even at ground level.
PX5000 lenses are head and shoulders better than anything else I have worn short of a welding mask if you really want to see in bright light. I have even briefly looked directly at the sun with these on without blinding myself.  They are unbeatable driving east at dawn or west at sunset.  I recently lost the pair I had been wearing for the last 10 years, and rued the day they disappeared.  My stock of three suddenly went to two.  I am so glad I found them again on Amazon.  I was afraid I'd need to make a trip to France to find a new pair.
summary: 26 years and still going strong with these

This is a aircrew flight boot; if you buy it for anything else, you picked the wrong shoe for a higher price.  Otherwise, this is a neat and lighter alternative to more traditional flying boots, especially for aircrew operating in locations where there is extreme heat.  When you are working on an airlift or tanker aircraft in the summer... and that aircraft is painted dark gray without the APU operating and with no ground cooling carts available, everything is hot, the cabin is an oven and this is where these boots earn their money as an approved piece of AFE.  Because of the internal GORTEX sock assembly in the shoe it runs approximately one half size too small.  That means that they run small.  I'm an 8.5 regular, so the size 9 regular fits me quite well.  Bought an 8.5 earlier and worked real hard to stretch them out and do a break-in; didn't work.  I gave the size 8.5 to my wife and she likes them just fine.  They are not for everyone!

reviewText: Picked these up for heavy-duty paintball (woodsball).  I've worn the boots for a total of 14 days since I bought them, including 4 game days and I'm happy with the purchase.  The boots are everything I expected out of Gore-Tex temperate weather boots:  Waterproof, warm (but not overly so), and solid.  I've been a size 9, D (normal) width in every shoe or boot I've owned in 15 years.  After reading other reviews, I ordered a half size larger (9.5) and the fit is perfect with lightweight wool blend boot socks on.  The boots definitely need to be broken in...I found them to be stiff at the start.  The soles are stiffer than I expected, but I don't find it to be an impediment.  By comparison, my old Bates Enforcers duty boots had the perfect blend of stiff support and flexibility in motion, but I'm quite happy not to have to polish my boots every other event now.
summary: Great boots, small fit...order a half size larger

This is my second pair of Belleville boots.  The first pair are tactical research 555 made by Belleville, which are essentially this model 693 but short 6 inch in desert tan.  I liked those boots so much after hundreds of miles on them in rough terrain in 2 years, that I decided to get myself these for the wet winter woods.  They feel fantastic, have excellent insoles, the outsoles are a light, but very durable Vibram Ibex sole, which grips in almost any conditions.  They fit nice and snug, the paracord laces cinch up tight, and they feel like you are wearing a tennis shoe.  As everyone stated, they run a half size small, so I'm usually a 10.5 US men's, but ordered the 11.0 Regular Mens and they fit perfectly.  I will update the review once I use them in the wet winter this year, but the Gore-tex bootie is so rugged, that I doubt there will be any leaking issues.  Also, being that it's summer now, I wore them yesterday and the weather was in the high 80's, and they were not too warm for summer either. I may wear them on a deer hunt in August to see how they do.
summary: Fantastic light, durable, and waterproof boot!

reviewText: I have to admit, I did not expect to like these sunglasses as much as I did. These are FANTASTIC sunglasses and for the price I paid they are even more AMAZING. The sunglasses are polarized and fit perfectly - they even have hinged arms that can flex out so they don't fit too tightly on your head. True story, this past weekend I went to a beach wedding here in Florida and wore these glasses. No fewer than 5 people grabbed them from me at some point during the day/night and put them on and told me they were the clearest glasses they ever wore. This actually got annoying later on in the evening when multiple people grabbed my shades and took them to the dance floor. You see, I was going boating the next morning and wanted to have my polarized sunglasses with me - normally I would just walk away from a $15 pair but NO...I stood there like an idiot and waited for these glasses to make their way way back to me. Glad I did because they were ideal on the water the next day and I still love them today. Don't hesitate - if you want a pair of polarized or even white framed sunglasses - buy these, you won't be disappointed.

I've ordered several pairs of these glasses in the past. I'm a kayak guide so I work on the water I really appreciate the polarization. But I use 'em hard, I break or lose them fairly often so I really appreciate their low cost. The pair I ordered most recently is different from previous pairs and are not as good. They are less durable, within a week both arms were already loose and giggly, and the frame is more shiny and slick, which I don't care for. Even the color of the lense is different, not as dark, but the polarization is about the same. For the price these are still a decent pair of shades, I just wish they were the ones I ordered originally, they used to be quite a bit better.
summary: Satisfactory for the price, but they were better in the past

I thought, due to the price, that this belt would be made out of cardboard. But, thankfully, it was exactly as shown - leather and nothing but. I bought both the brown and the black. Very nice looking and very adjustable because of all of the double holes.

This belt is perfect for my jeans, the leather is very rich looking. The most wonderful thing is that you cannot go wrong with the size which makes it very comfortable as you can adjust. I am very happy with it. It arrived right on time and it was everything the vendor said and more.

I originally gave this item 5 stars, but have since changed it to 4 stars after ordering/receiving another size belt and seeing how inconsistent the items are between sizes.
**********************************************************************************************************************
I have been wearing this belt probably 2-3x a week for almost six months and it's wonderful! The grommets are just fine, the belt hasn't come apart in any places, and the "missing holes" that others complain about don't look bad at all--in fact, I never even noticed it (on my belt it's about 3" or barely three sets of grommet holes which would normally be covered up with the overhang--see photo). That said, it is starting to get slightly worn where I usually place the buckle, but that's to be expected with pretty much any belt.

And I'd say that it runs big. I originally ordered the XL when I had about a 42" waist and it was big enough to wear 80's style. Now that I've lost weight and have a 38" waist, I have about 8" overhang and it's annoying so I'm back to order a smaller size (I could just cut this one down but for the price I'll just order a smaller one) so I'll be ordering a Medium which I hope fits correctly.

The XL is 50" long from tip of silver buckle to the end of the leather.

EDITED 3/19/16 TO ADD: I received the Medium belt and it was way too small. The M is 40" long from the tip of the silver buckle to the end of the leather. So, size 14 jeans, 190#, needs a size Large.

EDITED 3/24/16 TO ADD: I received the Large belt and it's actually just about right. It is 45.5" long from the tip of the silver buckle to the end of the leather and once buckled, there's about 3-4" of overhang. HOWEVER, the holes are spaced ever-so-slightly differently than the XL belt! I thought I was imagining it at first BECAUSE WHY WOULD THEY BE DIFFERENT? But when I placed the belts next to each other it became obvious (see photo). For every nine sets of holes in the XL belt, the L belt only has eight. That might not seem like that big of a deal, but it was enough for me to notice when I tried to buckle the belt for the first time. Also, as you can see in another picture, the L belt has MUCH more "empty" space (space without holes) on the belt than the XL did. I could barely notice it on the XL belt when I was wearing it, but it's much more noticeable on the L belt.

All that said, it's still a great belt for the price. But because of the inconsistencies I've lowered rating to four stars.
summary: Great belt for the price! Still looks good after wearing 2-3x a week for 6 months. Inconsistent details between sizes.

I had been having one heck of a time finding some bedroom slippers that would fit my feet and not slip off AND not have terrible reviews when I took a chance on this pair after reading reviews for hours. Happily hey fit the bill rather nicely.  In 2010 I had surgery on my left foot and my foot swole up to a size that now requires a 7E width in a street shoe.  My size before that was a 10 1/2 EEE.

One of my big problems with diabetic neuropathy is that my shoes easily slip off my feet since I can no longer feel them.. it's amazing what happens when you lose your feeling - shoes, and socks, just slip right off your feet without you even knowing it.  Anyway, I needed a shoe wide enough to handle a 7E width on one foot, while staying on a 3E right foot.  Though about one size too long, they stay on the majority of the time and fit both feet comfortably.

My biggest problem with the shoes is the design.  Due to the curvature of the shoes, it is very difficult to tell which is left and which is right.  In fact, they look rather like a pair of big ol' clown shoes, as one person said.  Other than the goofy look, they work for me at a price that didn't break the bank!  I recommend them.

**** UPDATE (10/15/2014)****  The heel is as loose and torn up as a 40 year old pair of elastic briefs already.  No longer recommend.

reviewText:
For the price, I would recommend the watch. It's pretty heavy and appears to be a well built metal timepiece. Because of it's simplicity (you push the top button once and count the outside lights for the hours (in blue) and a second time for the minutes (in red)), it's not the most amazing watch ever made. But, for 12 bucks, I have no complaints.
A couple things to note, the metal links are mildly darker than they appear in the picture. Also, the pictures posted by the seller are a little misleading. In the pictures, the watch looks like it has a solid black face that then lights up to give you the time. It actuality, you can see the 12 outer quadrilaterals and 4 inner white triangles at all times. These then turn blue / red when pushed to give you the time.
Another reviewer mentioned it running small. Im a pretty chunky guy and it fit on my wrist with space to spare.
And, thank you to oldgoldone for instructions as to how to set the watch because instructions are not included.
Finally, it took about a month to get the states from Hong Kong. So, if you're buying it as gift, please order it early.

reviewText: buyer beware: do not buy-in to clever marketing and get your hopes up for the fit or quality of Tommy John underwear or socks. Both the underwear and socks are tight-fitting and restrictive to circulation. The Tommy John "best fit guarantee" or "no adjustment needed" slogans are rendered untrue by the fine-print, which is not clearly listed while ordering online, or listed on electronic/paper receipts. In addition, the customer service representatives hide behind the fine-print and give generic form responses while trying to resolve any dissatisfaction

I am 65 years of age, and throughout I have worn many pair of underwear but none for $30.00 a PAIR.  After hearing their commercials I decided to try a couple of pair. If you want comfy underwear at a cost of cost $30.00 /pr  that you can wear maybe 12 times Tommy John is for you.
After wearing and washing a pair approx. 8 times the seam on the bottom of the boxer brief leg came off.  I explained to them the situation saying I have many pair of underwear ( Jockey , Hanes ) and do not wear Tommy John all that often. I even sent them a photo of the damaged mdse.
They asked me how I washed and dried them , if I used them while playing sports.  Can you imagine their product is good for just walking around and sitting, all that for $30 plus dollars a pair.  Although I did receive this particular pair as a gift from my wife ( 3 pair ) a year prior I explained it was a few months until I wore them , and then infrequently.  Only 8 times at the most and never used the dryer only air dry.
Their customer service offered me a $10.00 credit . I told them  they could keep it because they lost someone who would never recommend or buy another pair.
summary: Expensive , poor quality , poor customer service

reviewText:
Having to deal temporary with crutches and carrying a purse sliding off my shoulder motivated me to find a convertible backpack style purse that had plenty of compartment and stylish enough to go anywhere. I found that in the BRIANA bag. It's large and has plenty of compartments to keep you organized. So many reasons to love the bag. This bag is soft and supple and not a stiff bag for being man made material. Tablet fits perfect in the bag. One of the featured I really liked was the Top Flap zippered compartment. I ended up using to put my sunglasses all the time. The zippered partition style compartment at times felt in the way when I really wanted to load the bag for traveling.  Another featured I liked was the the flap covered that hid the main zipper. So even if you use it as a backpack someone can't just stick their hands into the main interior of the bag. (not a failsafe deterrent for expert but helps).
This bag was a temp solution for me while I was using crutches but love it enough to continue using it. I looked at other comparable bags but you would have to pay twice to three times as much for a similar style. So far it's been able to take the abuse without losing stitches or tearing. The only negative comment that I will make on the bag is the particular color I chose was the mustard. The pigment is not smooth consistent color it has blotches of over pigments in some of the veins so certain areas have a more orange hue than mustard.
summary: Perfect for going hands-free with many compartments!

First is that it is not designed to fit all luggage well, when you use the pull-out panel that allows it to grip the bars of a rolling bag's extended handles.  If you have a non-Briggs & Riley bag, it won't line up well and isn't very secure.  Which brings me to issues #2:  the pull-out panel just pulled completely off, so that I can't attach it to my luggage at all.  Now I have to send it back in for repair (there are no stores to take it to in Austin, which isn't a small town.)  I have to do this at my expense.  Poor design.

I really liked my previous Briggs & Riley rolling computer bag, but I started a new job and wanted something a little slimmer.  Overall it's a very well-built and well-designed product with only one complaint.  The lining gets caught in the zipper almost every time I zip up the main compartment from the sides.  I've learned to be extremely careful, but still it's a hassle when you're zipping up at and airport because they're boarding a plane.

You certainly get what you pay for with these. I can't complain about the price, they are very affordable, and they were shipped quickly. I got one of each color, with some that had slight variations, such as three different shades of pink. Overall, I got a light and a dark of each color with a crystal, an AB, and a hematite. The bar is a bit long but i have a nose that can accommodate that. I wouldn't recommend these for folks with thin nostrils or a septum that extends below the outer edge of the nostril. The bar and curve will be regularly visible, and metallic boogies aren't really cute.

My main issue is with the stones. They are glued on, but some are glued on at very wonky angles, looking like they will fall off at any minute, sideways, crooked, off-center. I am also super bummed because my favorite color stone has a large dab of glue on the outside of the metal cup, the part that rests against my nose. I had a HUGE allergic reaction to the glue, and I tried on 3 separate occasions to make sure it was the glue I was reacting to. The skin around the piercing became red and inflamed, painful to the touch, all that other good stuff that looks like an infection. That didn't happen with any of the other pieces which didn't have glue on the outside. If you don't have sensitive skin, or you get pieces without glue spills, you should be fine. I haven't had any reactions to the metal itself, which was my main concern.

All in all, it's a good bargain and the stones are pretty, but there are a couple things to watch out for. Definitely don't expect to get 20 pieces in pristine condition.
summary: Bargain price, but crooked stones and allergic reaction to the glue

I use this watch every day as a medic, and I'm on my second one (last one was the identical watch, from some other chinese maker.) the last one simply reached the end of its battery after a couple years and by then the plastic lens was scratched up (I am not a good judge of a watchface's durability since I somehow can scratch sapphire glass faced watches in my line of work, but the watch has never become so scratched that it was unreadable, I simply replaced it because it was so cheap, so I wouldn't say you should be concerned.) so I just decided a new one was worth it. Both have kept immaculate time, the function buttons are easy to use and having standard hands for tracking time on a heart or respiratory rate, along with a stopwatch for tracking I.V. flow is excellent, as is having the digital 12/24 hour clock (easily switched between) gives me a perfect snapshot (seconds are clear and in the center digital box) for writing down times of procedures. I have tiny, tiny wrists for a man, and this watch both fits very well and is unbelievably comfortable. it is also adjustable to a much bigger wrist as well. Overall build quality is excellent, rear battery cover is screwed on with four phillips head screws, I can easily submerge the watch for handwashing without any concerns. Lots of compliments as well. Overall, I'll be buying this watch every couple years (on the whole, cheaper than a $200 watch that lasts ten years)  until I can no longer buy it, because there is literally not a single complaint I have about it. All the digital displays are crystal clear and the illuminate function illuminates all the digital displays. If this watch came with a proper sapphire glass face, I'd argue that it would be easily worth $80-100. I've been buying cheap chinese watches for a while since I'm just too hard on watches to spend any more, and this is the only one that truly has no "quirks" inherent to the idea of a dirt cheap watch.

I love everything about this tie.  It is made from reclaimed wood in San Francisco and as such, every tie made should be unique due to the individual wood patterns.  Mine for example has a pinstripe like pattern with some curves, and three small knots near the top.  It's a very simple design and I'm honestly a little surprised I haven't seen these before.  The tie is separated into segments so it can flex, and has elastic bands running through the entire tie to hold it together and secure it to your neck.  My one and only complaint is that I noticed a slight crack on the corner of a segment, however this was easily fixed with wood glue and now you can't tell there was ever anything wrong with it.  I would highly recommend this tie and do fully intend on buying more.  This company also makes wood bowties if that is more to your liking.

If you have a shorter torso, this tie may not work as well for you. I'd give it a shot just in case because it's so stinkin' cool, but just keep that in mind. Also, the stretchy cord was mildly visible at the collar of the shirt, but that could be because of the style of collar (cutaway) on my husband's shirt. MWC, if this watch is truly representative of their entire product line, makes nothing but quality.  Furthermore, it's quality at a reasonable price.  Who has the cash to pay hundreds of dollars for a Luminox?  Honestly?  And they look like you're wearing a portion of the terminator on your wrist.

The watch has some weight to it and seems to be amazingly durable thus far.  I was somewhat skeptical of the nylon band, but it operates perfectly.  I trimmed some off to fit my wrist then flame-singed it with a lighter to prevent further unravelling.  I am one who does not like leather for a work/field watch and rubberized bands simply don't hold up.  Also in the durability category, I LOVE the genuine real glass, yes real glass, they employ for the watch face.  It does not scratch and does indeed give a classic, streamlined look as advertised.

I have tried watch after watch including Swiss Army models made by Victorinox and Wenger.  They suck.  Plain and simple.  I'd go with an MWC model.  Trust me on this one.  You will not be sorry.  I work in the medical profession and wear it at work as well as in the field.  It does well in both arenas.  Check out their website ([...] to get a good look at all the available products.

Its small and relatively light as advertise.  It holds up very nicely when there are at least three bills.  I use it only for money and not credit cards and it works great for me.  It is not spring-loaded as I originally thought but thats ok, it works just fine.  I have already received some nice compliments on this money clip.  I am definitely happy with this purchase.  It definitely looks like it will hold up for some time.  And even if it doesnt, I don't mind because it was so cheap.  I highly recommend this money clip!

I only need prescription glasses for reading, not distance.  The problem I've encountered is out driving and needing to look at directions, or the GPS on my cell phone, but can't read it without my reading glasses!  I thought about getting bi-focal sunglasses but that costs a fortune.  So I researched clip-on, to put on a nice pair of bi-focals (that I actually inherited from my mother).  I knew I wanted good polarization and many clip-ons aren't polarized (same with sunglasses).  From reviews, the Coccons always came up on top, and these were polarized.  I did appreciate the Cocoon charts and info regarding proper fit.  If you pay attention to all that, you'll have clip-ons that fit perfectly.  Mine do, no slipping around.  And they really are well made, and the polarization is wonderful. And, if I have to look down at directions or my phone, I can read it fine.  It's a great alternative for people who need bi-focals for close reading.  They look good too.
summary: I LOVE these, really quality polarizing!

I've had my new Slimware Flat Buckle Belt for a couple of weeks. It is perfectly flat and does not rub against my clothes, so no more little holes in my tops! It's well made with quality materials and is quick and easy to adjust for size. If you're looking for a belt that doesn't have a bulky buckle, I highly recommend this one by Hartwares. I love it!

I wanted a belt to keep my pants up but also that wouldn't show the bulge from the buckle. I bought one of the plastic kind and although it was flat, it was a little too pliable and I still had trouble keeping my pants in place. This one is much more sturdy and so far is working out fine.
While my pants don't fall down my bum, they still slip down. I still need to frequently adjust my pants/belt. Better than the alternative.

The belt is decently made, and it is so "insignificant", that it is hardly visible. There is no bulky buckle. Adjustment is simple, on both ends. Velcro holds really well. The very important fact for me is that it is made in the USA.

Update 11/14/2014:  I love this belt.  The 2014 version has an easier plastic clip action for the buckle, which is even more comfortable.  Also, I like the latest "pleather" look.  It's the only belt I ever wear - no belly bulge and adjustable.

Usually I skip wearing a belt, as the buckle just makes my stomach look fatter - and who needs that??  But this belt is awesome - a perfectly flat buckle, no extra bulk through your jean loops.  Great for anyone who wants to look 5 pounds thinner, no dieting required.  It even comes with adjustment tricks so you can size it perfectly.  I highly recommend and plan to order more to give as gifts.  Note:  The sizing isn't as straightforward as it looks, since the belt is unisex.  I didn't realize this when I ordered off the website. Since the belt is adjustable, it wasn't a problem.  But next time I'll be aware that a medium-sized female can order a "small" in this belt size.

In the US, children's sleepwear is supposed to fit tightly or be coated in a chemical to make them flame resistant. I'll take initially tight pjs over chemicals any day. I am very impressed with these and compare the quality to a those sold at a well known children's store where they are sold at a much higher price point. I have since ordered multiple pairs in multiple sizes for my children and plan to purchase them again.

UPDATE 4/18/2016

I had bought these 2/22/2016 and they literally broke yesterday. Where they broke was actually at the hinge and it was the little metal hinge that broke, not the plastic.

The hinge snapped just from opening them up. They had been dropped at one time a while ago and one of the lenses had popped out, but the frame didn't crack and I was able to snap the lense back in, so that was a plus, but the hinge snapping is still a bit disappointing.

I have purchased another pair though as I have looked through similarly priced sunglases at Walmart and Target and like the look and style of these way more than anything they have.

reviewText: I was so excited about these boots because they were exactly what I was looking for.  The reviews were pretty good and everyone said how comfortable they were.  I normally do not buy boots for $24 because the quality will not be there, I prefer real leather. I figured I would give them a try because they were super cute.  Once I got them, they fit exactly as they should. I ordered true to size,  I am an 8, and they fit perfectly. I really love the zippers on both sides and the buckles on the back. My problems far out way the pro's.  These boots are not comfortable at all.  There is no insole cushioning or arch support what so ever.  The way the other reviews raved how comfortable they were, I was extremely disappointed.  My biggest problem is that after a month the heal ripped completely off from the upper part of the boot!  I know I shouldn't expect much out of a pair of boots for $24, but I did expect them to last longer than 1 MONTH!!  I have learned my lesson and just put forth the money for a quality, real leather boot that are completely awesome!
summary: Buyer's Beware! The price is right, but if you are looking for quality, this is NOT the boot for you.

This is a really attractive sweater, and the fit flatters. However, as the owner of several other Aran Crafts sweaters that wear like iron, I am disappointed that this is on the delicate side. Maybe it's the Merino wool, which is softer than the (admittedly somewhat scratchy) wool in my other Aran Crafts garments, or maybe it's the fabric, which is less dense than that of the other Aran Crafts in my closet. But this snags on everything. and after a couple of weeks of moderate wear, the fabric is pilling where the undersides of the arms brush the sides of the body.

I would return it but it's just too darn pretty to part with.
I LOVE this sweater! Its perfect and practical. Dress it up or down. Super, super warm.

Pros:  Unique pattern & style, warmth, longer length is wonderful for tall women, cool zipper pull.  The "waist" stitching is very flattering on my figure.

Cons:  Cheap zipper - it takes several tries to get the connection so the zipper will close.  After that, it's fine, but it's difficult almost every time. (This is what disappoints me/ticks me off the most about this sweater.  For the money, give me a YYK zipper and no hassles!
The VVK zipper is a cheap knockoff.  A quotation below is from the VVK zipper webpage.  Having just looked this up, I'm getting more and more disappointed.
"Stock Zippers! Nylon and Derlin Zippers for only 2 Eur / kg; Metal Zippers for only 5 Eur / kg ... VVK production is tested and gained I class OEKO-TEX sertificate."
(Read: Authentic Irish Sweaters with cheap Chinese zippers.)

The cost of 2.2 pounds of VVK zippers is about $2.36.

A single 18" YKK zipper is $6.25 and is top quality.
This cheap zipper is outrageous on a piece of clothing this expensive.

Color: On my monitor, it looks like it's brown.  It's actually charcoal.
Also, there are random red plastic pieces and random white threads woven into the pattern.

Fit:  it fits quite well in the chest and is true to size.  However, it looks like a *bell* around my hips.  It's far beyond the measurement it should be.

I am 5' 11", 200 lbs, 46x37x44 (approximately).

Pattern:  Looking at the photo with the white turtleneck sweater below, you can not see the white turtleneck through the pattern.  That is not the case and the white clearly shows through.  I am not pleased with that. I think the elbows will wear out faster than you would expect.

"Coat" is wayyy to generous a term for this sweater.
I thought it was a sweater coat, but the fact that the pattern is loosely stitched and you can see the top you're wearing underneath makes the statement "sweater coat" untrue.
It may be fine for an evening chill while sitting on the deck, but I would not trust it to be sufficient to wear throughout a fall football game in its entirety.

Merino wool:  The tag inside touts the history and softness of Merino wool.
The history may be correct for what they thought was soft hundreds of years ago.
I LOVE wool.  Love it!  But...

This is scratchy and if you are sensitive to touch sensations, you won't like it.  Do count on wearing a turtleneck under it if you decide to take the leap.
I did expect it to be much softer that it is.  It feels like the wool sweaters I bought in Greece in 1994 that were made 100% by hand by women in remote villages.
That being said, this is authentic wool.  It feels like those sweaters do.  That feeling is not for everyone.

This has a more rustic look and feel than you would expect based on the refined look of the model in the photo.
It is not soft.
It does look like light colored dog hair is all over it (it's the wool, not dog hair, but that's what it looks like).

I began this review at 3.5 stars just because I love the style so much. Then as I wrote my review, I dropped it to 3 stars.
After looking up the zippers, I'm dropping it to 3 stars.

Why all this fuss about zippers?
If you're in a rush, this will slow you down and you will get frustrated.  I would end up giving up if I were in a hurry and leave with it unzipped or swap it for a different outer layer.

If your clothing gets stuck, cheap zippers are harder to correct and more likely to tear up your garment.

No, I don't work in the zipper industry or own any stock.  I like excellent products and am so tired of the "Big Mac" affect where the photos look great but you end up with a slipshod version of what was pictured.

Overall, that's my impression.

Remember, I love wool. I have a lot of it - I'm always cold.

For the kind of money being charged for this piece, you could look up a boutique in Ireland and get the real deal for a comparable price and get way better quality.
That's what I'm going to do.

Happy shopping...somewhere else.

This design from Xotic Eyes has potential to be good, but as it stands... it's in need of massive improvement.
It's very difficult to get the product off the backing. It's thin, delicate and very very sticky so while trying to remove the item you have it sticking to your fingertips constantly and have to really try not to allow it to stick to itself... it doesn't peel off nicely...you have to pull and that force required to lift it off the backing makes it even harder to keep the product in good condition.
Once you have it off... it's now very difficult to apply it. It's all in one piece... and if you don't lay it on your face perfectly the very first time (almost impossible) then you will find it's horrible to try and reposition it. It got stuck to my eyelid so I tried to reposition it because being able to see is kind of important and while trying to adjust the product, it stuck to itself, my face and fingers resulting in a wadded-up ball of Xotic Eyes crap.
I tried with this product..  I've had great success with other Xotic Eyes items... but this was a difficult ridiculous mess that I ended up throwing in the trash.
I saw one user who recommended cutting the product in half horizontally and I would absolutely take that advice if you purchase this item. Cutting the two large pieces into 4 will help you avoid some of the extremely frustrating issues associated with this item. BUT, make sure you cut the eye pieces in half before you peel them off the backing... they're very sticky and delicate.
Overall I can't recommend this product. Purchase the Ice Queen or Villian eyes instead.
summary: Nice idea, but needs a change of design...

Great wallet. The best I've ever owned. I really wasn't into upscale wallets in the past, but was getting tired of my obsolete-trend design wallet that was also very thick and wide for no reason. I used to keep it in my back pocket but it would give me pain on my opposite butt cheek, so I have sense switch to front pocket wear indefinitely. I also use this technique to ward off pick-pocketers, because nobody in their right mind is going to try to reach inside of your front pocket to gain access to your wallet.

This slim fit, front pocket wallet is excellent because it has a hard leather outer shell. I have owned the wallet for a couple of months now and unfortunately it is bending a bit on the corners, but with the cards inside it keeps the middle crisp and firm. I am glad they did not go with a softer and bendable leather as the wallet would not look as sleek and also be harder to remove from your pocket since it would contour to your thigh, and also generally would not withstand the trials of daily use. The interior leather--I got the eye-catching orange version, which has unfortunately seemed to have been discontinued--is a bit thin and soft for my liking. It is great for being able to easily remove and insert cards, but it seems they may be able to tear more easily and not have enough tensile strength to really grip onto the cards so that they don't accidentally fall out. So far this has not been a problem, and it surprisingly grips the credit cards better than i originally expected.

The money clip is "money," aka genius. It has a locking mechanism that is quite satisfying to click open and shut, and it is just tight enough to hold all the dollar bills you need. The lock is a sense of security and that it will hold every time. I have not dealt with money clips before, but used to think they were tacky or for old guys. This money clip is sexy and modern and minimally elegant. It makes the wallet even lower-profile, since most of the time I am not carrying cash anyway. It is truly the design for the future generation: more credit card dependent and no cash, and not too many "loyalty cards" or coupons.

Sophisticated design and quality product. I also like that it was designed in Australia, because I feel Australians have good taste. I'm not sure where it is made, hopefully in the same country but I doubt it, since it does not advertise specifically.

The gift box is one of the best gift boxes I've opened: comparable to the quality craftsmanship of the iphone box. The presentation is really half the product, and I must confess I bought it because I thought it would be fun to own a small piece of astroturf/synthetic grass. My complaint here is that the grass is cut a bit small and leaves negative space in the box, and seems like more of an afterthought. I would buy this wallet again, but I think mine will last for at least a decade, as that's almost as long as I've had my last wallet, and I'm more proud to carry this one.

-Ken Flemming
Author, "How to Get a Job in Video Games"
summary: Excellent wallet for the future man

reviewText:
If you're reading this product review you're a soccer player.  So quit reading and just buy these damn shoes before they discontinue them.  I already bought two pairs, these and the ones with black and purple styling.

Seriously, buy two pairs, you won't regret it.

PROS:
Amazingly light, amazingly
Great fit to the form of your foot (I've high arches AND wide feet, no problem)
Stylish
Very good traction on hard fields, grass and even wet turf

CONS:
Why did you NIKE bastards take so long to make something as good as this!  Just keep on doing it!

REAL CONS:
Because they are soooo light and form fitting, they will not protect you from morons that will cleat you--ouch on top!
Likewise, if you're an enforcer type player and are brutish in dispensing hard tackles and getting stuck in on 50/50 balls, these won't punish the opponent as well as real cleats... (but if you were such a meat head you probably can't read reviews very well and aren't viewing this part of my comment)
If you compete and get cleated a lot by a**holes in the competition (see above), these will likely not last a full season (but I've not seen any evidence of seams splitting or tearing at the construction welds in my previous pairs) because these shoes are not as durable as real leather and will tear on top or wherever you take direct and consistent abuse.

And this means even though you want to hold the ball and touch it 30 times with these on, don't dribble like a ball hog and get dispossessed all the time...

Geez!  Pass me the friggin' ball once in awhile, will you!

I wear a 9.5 US on all my shoes and Venzo's 9.5 fit perfectly! Do not get mislead by reviews; I ordered half a size smaller (9) and they hurt. Had to return them and order my size (9.5).
Go to any shoe store, have your foot sized and order that.

What I liked:
1) Very nice combo for the money spent. You will not get a pair of pedals, shoes and cleats for $75 shipped anywhere else ;)
2) They seem to be good quality and they are really light (comparable to high end shoes).
3) Shoe size is spot on!

What I did not like:
1) The pedals, like most new pedals, came torqued incorrectly so they do not spin as freely as they should. I will have to disassemble them and torque the nuts correctly to avoid premature wear on the internal bearings. I will need to buy a special tool to take them apart or have that done at a bike shop.
 2) Shoes have holes for both mountain bike and road bike cleats. My left shoe had the metal Mountain Bike cleat receiver lose and since I am using Road bike cleats it was rattling inside the sole like a maraca (very annoying). I had to remove the insole and get to the metal receiver from inside the shoe and glue it to the sole.

I highly recommend these shoes and pedals and I would buy again. Thanks Amazon!
summary: Nice! Fits as expected. Requires tweaking.

reviewText: Purchased these for my husband. They are a smidge small and not comfortable when walking but when he's riding his bike, he says they are perfect. He has learned to put these shoes on very last, right before getting on the bicycle instead of when he first gets to the park.

Shortly after I got my road bike, I ordered this Wellgo pedal and Venzo shoe set from Amazon.

I assumed because I was a newbie that was why I was having problems unclipping. I practiced and practiced. I've made a number of successful rides with the clipless pedals and shoes. However, even these rides that I call successful include many unsuccessful attempts to unclip. The shoe was stuck in the pedal even though I had rotation and attempted to pull out of the pedal.

I've adjusted both the shoes and the pedals. I re-read the Amazon reviews each time I had problems, and there are plenty of reviews that say the same thing, even reviews left by people who claim to have a lot of experience riding with clipless pedals.

I've continued to try to give these pedals and shoes many chances, but finally after riding around in my yard looking for a soft place to slow land because I could NOT get out of the pedals, I have chosen to give up hope on the Wellgo pedals and Venzo shoes.

I'm not here to bad mouth the set. I really wanted it to work. However, I'm finally done with jeopardizing my safety to try to get these bargain shoes and pedals to work.

reviewText:
Reading other reviews, I think I expected something different from what other people knew they were getting. But rereading the description, I think I'm justified in finding it inaccurate.

I have these pants from Express that I love. They're jeggings, in that they are totally comfy and stretchy, but they don't look a thing like leggings. They just look like jeans. That's what I wanted out of these pants too.

Well, heads up: These pants do not look like jeans. They look like leggings. The fabric feels and stretches like leggings. The stitching screams leggings. The button at the top looks like the cheesy plastic buttons on children's clothes. There is nothing jean-like about them. Fake pockets and zip flies are not unique to jeans, and therefore, in my opinion, do not give you license to say that something is "like jeans." For something to be like jeans, it needs to be able to imitate the defining factor in jeans, which is *denim.* If you say "like jeans" and don't mean "like denim" you're deliberately misleading people. These are not jeggings. These are leggings. Let's call a spade a spade.

I was so appalled at the cheap look of these pants that I didn't even try them on. However, I did notice that they appear to be very low rise as well. I don't tend to find pants that sit on or below my hip bones comfortable to wear, in the sense that they are very restricting in the crotch area and I'm constantly hiking them up. Such a low rise in pants with this kind of fabric makes me think that they put the wearer at serious risk for camel-toe.

Given that I am a self-respecting human being who does not wear leggings out of the house pretending they're pants, I could not keep these. I had to send them back.
Will not buy again

I'm not the biggest skirt fan, I usually just prefer dresses, but I really like that 1950s look, so I bought this dress. I would give it 5 stars, but there were some minor set backs, all in all it's a great skirt. The image displays the real life one pretty accurately, but I'll go into some brief details about it:

Pros: It fits as expected, I wear a size 4 in women's jeans and bought the medium knowing it'd be snug based upon the style. It's a great color that you can pretty much wear with any top if you're willing to experiment with some bold colors! The frontal bow design was a bit flat from packaging, but starting to ruffle out once I wore it a few times.

Cons: I wanted to give this a 5 start rating just because I really love this skirt, but I want to be realistic and honest. These types of skirts are supposed to zip up to your upper hip, pretty much meeting up with your belly button. But I noticed when I walk in this skirt that it gradually starts to slip up and eventually turn into a super mini skirt. So it can get awkward when you're trying to walk around in public and tugging at your skirt the whole time. Also, the material is pretty sheer. I highly advise not wearing anything black under there and recommend wearing a light colored thong. If you want to wear nothing under there, go for it, not really my cup of tea but be ready to flash a few people as the skirt starts to rise!

So to recap, the skirt is great, fits as expected, matches the image, but rises when you walk and is made from a pretty sheer material, so be ready to hide those undies.

reviewText: My boyfriend loved it the minute he saw it on me.  Great bra.  Comfortable and flirty. Love it!

Love, love, love this sweater. The wide arm openings and the easy access tank are a perfect combination for nursing. If I plan on being out running errands all day this is my go-to top. Being large chested, it can be a challenge to feed discreetly but this sweater makes it so easy. The bottom of the sweater does stretch out as you wear it but the utility of the sweater far outweighs this small nuance for me.

I ordered the charcoal gray, which is half the price of the darker gray and the cream color. Now I know why, because it's sewn all wrong. The fit is very different from what the picture shows, and the result is definitely not flattering. I wish I didn't have to send it back, because the fabric is so high quality, it feels really good and warm - I can understand why they're charging almost $100 for the other colors. If I had $100 to spend on a nursing sweater, I would definitely go for one of the other colors because it's a nice piece. By the way, responding to what the other reviewer said, you actually could easily detach the shirt from the sweater and have two nice separate pieces. It's only connected by a little bit of thread at the neck. And the nursing openings are nice and easy to use.

Two e-mails, two phone calls, and two months to get the jacket, and it was not the color ordered.  They were kind enough to throuw in a scarf because of the delay, but still got it wrong; we asked for black and got red.  We decided it would be too much trouble to try and exchange.  But it turns out the jacket is exceptionally good quality with a lot of nice features, and worth the high price.  The material is water repellent and light but substantial, the lining is cleverly revealed at the collar, the placket on the zip front is well designed, the pleat in the back is stylish, the cuff has great detail.  So.... I can recommend the jacket but only if you stay on top of the selller and make sure they ship your order as requested.

This bathing suit has a few pros that might make it worth buying:
-nice material, not sheer or too thin, lined top, will dry fast
-vibrant color
-really pretty beading

Some neutral points to consider:
-the jewles aren't green (or bright pink) they are cream colored. Why do they look green in the picture? Because it is totally photoshopped to change the color of the suit, and not an actual picture of the "green" suit. However, with this in mind, the jewels were actually much prettier in person. They have little diamonds in them and are so delicate and girly. Probably my favorite part of the suit.
-the green color is actually teal. It is so pretty, if you like teal then you will not be disappointed. But it is not green at all, it is more blue than green.

The cons:
-way too small. The cups are very very close together, and the bottoms are realllllly little. I am 5'1, 125lbs and I had way more booty showing in the back than I was comfortable with. Also, the cups are rigidly formed, so if your chest doesn't line up with them you end up looking very strange, with lots of side boob and too oddly fitting cups hovering in the middle of your chest. This top will NOT work for busty women, it is simply too small and rigidly formed.
- the worst part, and the reason I am returning this rather than giving it to a friend, is that the plastic liner that is in the bottoms (the sanitary liner they put in all suits for when people try them on) was obviously in there for a very long time, because when I tried to remove it all the advise stayed behind on the suit. It was like baked on. It was very sticky and I couldn't think of any way to get a giant strip of adhesive off the bottoms, so I'm returning this. Almost immediately after trying to remove the plastic liner the bottoms started to get stuck in the adhesive left behind and get all gummed up. Not cool.

So, three stars for the fabric, jewled accents, and for any girl petite enough to pull this off. But ultimately a bad fit for my body and a defective product.

I love it! Looks just like the picture! Wore it the first day to work. I work 12 hour shifts. The chain with the clasp stretched and came apart once, but I was leaning on the back of a chair and putting pressure on it. Easy fix with some needle nose pliars. What I love about this kind of jewelry is that it is not stretchy. I bought a chocker necklace at Hot Topic for about 5 times the price of this and the lace was elastic and after the first time I wore it I have to tie it then clasp it to make it sit on my neck correctly now. It's such a hassle that I rarely wear it. But this holds its shape. I do a lot of paperwork/writing/typing so the chain that makes it the slave bracelet bothers me. I am thinking about taking it off and use it as a separate ring and bracelet. I have several pieces of this jewelry so far and I can mix and match it to my hearts content. The price makes it worth it as one piece or two. I have not had the problem of the 'gem' separating from the rest yet, but a dab of good glue that you probably already have laying around your house would fix that. In my experience with cheaper jewelry, this is worth it. Whether you buy it to wear once with a costume, or like me you wear it on a more regular basis, I would recommend it. (I can see, however, if you have a very skinny wrist it might be too big. Or if you have a very wide wrist it may look a bit odd if you wear it as jewelry instead of a costume. It is crochet though so for a skinny wrist it can hook through that. And it has a long chain at the clasp so it could potentially fit a very wide wrist.) One thing to bear in mind, it takes several weeks to arrive. So if you want it for a special occasion order early.

The design is perfect. I have mine filled with 5 credit cards, 2 RFID pass cards, a driver's license, credit card sized multi-tool, a book of field notes and a small pen, and it has plenty of room to spare.

Received it a few days ago, and so far so good. The quality of the leather and construction is good overall, and very good for the money. The slots are pretty tight at the outset, but I expect that will work itself out over the next few weeks. The RFID blocking material makes a bit of a crinkling noise, especially when the wallet first comes out of the box and isn't full of cards. I was afraid it might make that noise when I moved around with the wallet in my pocket, but that does not appear to be a problem.

reviewText: This is without a doubt the single most practical purchase I have ever made. I keep it in my living room, and it really ties the room together. Plus, it doubles as a wonderful coat rack! And when my kids get a little out of line, I send them to the "gollum time out podium" they have to chill with him for a couple of hours and well he's a firm disciplinarian. To put it simply, this statue has done wonders for my life. I also sleep a little easier knowing he's out there in my living room. Sometimes I even put him in my bed. He does what no nightlight ever could. So, this is a MUST BUY! Well worth the $600 spent!!!!

Gollum, is, shall we say, creepy. He's not yet housebroken and when he cooks for me it tastes like fish. Haha. Anyway, he's not easily breakable, so no need to worry. His eyes are hand-painted (unlike his counterpart, Smeagol, in the limited edition statue produced by New Line for the Two Towers release). If you look closely at the roots of his hair they appear to be stapled on. The base isn't as solid as it looks. I'm not sure what kind of material it is but it's not a real rock, and I'm worried about damaging it so I don't use it (Gollum's hands and feet screw onto it). That's the only 'flaw' with this. One tip: Hide it from children.

reviewText:
I had a good experience for two-thirds of my Next Level purchases; this was one of them.

I assumed these were juniors sizing, so they fit like size large on someone who usually gets a junior's medium. They don't work for me. These seemed to be very well made (good stitching, no errant threads, felt very cotton-y), fit almost exactly like the photos. I won't be buying them in a small because the fit was far more stiff, not stretchy or more form-fitting. It literally fit quite like the picture. It has proper stretch, but it is definitely more of a woman's shirt than it is a junior's, too much cotton, not enough polyester or something. It was fairly soft, again, given its cotton nature (I did not check the tag for the exact ingredients), though not as soft as I'd like. I also like my sleeves to be more 'capped' than this typical short-sleeve - I expected the fit to be different on me because of the not-stretchy fabric and size of the not-junior's shirt. The shoulders were almost constructed in my opinion (like they'd been on wire hangers or had padding in the shoulders); I didn't think it was very flattering. The shirts were extremely long - almost a dress for me (5'7") and I don't care for that. It's one thing to cover your behind in jeans when you squat down, it's another to be nearly a dress but not long enough to wear with jeggings, etc. I didn't see the point of having so long and cumbersome a shirt. Also, some shirts cost more than others; I'm not sure why.

I returned them and received an email saying that I would get my refund, but I did not have to return the shirts because it would cost me to ship them. So I got my refund and got to keep two of three shirts!

IMPORTANT NOTE: I attempted to return these shirts FOUR TIMES. After their promise to get back to you within 48 hours, which never happened. The second time, I was refunded for the two shirts (and got to keep them). The third time, I received an entirely differently email with an unpaid returns label. The fourth time, I sent a specific, polite email through Amazon, detailing my problem. I said that I was confused and irritated and simply wanted my money back ($6 for shipping on a $9 shirt?). I informed them that I had not yet posted a review on Amazon. I HAVE NOT HEARD BACK! I HAVE NOT RECEIVED A REFUND FOR THE THIRD SHIRT!
summary: Apparent quality women's shirt; horrible returns experience!

At the time of writing this review I now own 4 pairs of Youth sized Vibram and I have to say I prefer the fit to the Adult sizes.

Generally I wear a 40 in Women's or a 39 in Men's in most styles of Vibrams. As sizing varies between the models they often have been too spacious in the toes for me. However I have consistently felt that the youth sizing Vibram are better fit and the price makes them totally worth it!

I order a size 41 in the Youth and they fit like a glove, the fact that I've never spent more than twenty bucks on a pair makes it even better!

I do have to say that the Youth models have the most basic KSO sole which has very little traction so if you're looking for Vibrams with soles made for hiking or heavier wear I wouldn't choose these. However these are great for both gym and casual wear! I love them and will be getting more!

reviewText:
Pros:
* Comes in my unusual size, which most swimsuits don't.
* Modest, but still really cute and flattering
* Underwire and proper bra support means I can be comfortable in or out of the water.
* Fits comfortably
* Good price
* Can be worn comfortably with or without straps (and stays up)

Cons:
* When pulling it on, the underwire pokes until properly situated
* After being in the water for a while, the weight of the water pulls the band and underwire down when I emerge.

All in all, I consider the cons to be perfectly understandable and not really an inconvenience at all. It's a cute, comfortable swimsuit that fits well even though my boobs and hips feel like they're at least a size or two bigger than my waist. I also like that it's modest enough that I can feel comfortable wearing it at church functions even for fairly conservative churches without judgment, but it's also very stylish.

If you, like me, are trying to figure out if it's worth the risk to spend this much money on a swimsuit bought online, my answer is yes.

My husband had to have this watch.  It took him some time to understand it and all that it does but he now wears it everyday and he loves it.  It fits as expected.  It is slightly heavy but it is a larger watch so that is expected.

The spare black rubber band makes this watch look so much better that the original band, and also fits better, more comfortably because of the increased number of graduations for band adjustment.  Also, the accessory band swivels at the attachment points with the watch, helping it feel more comfortable.

Already I froze it at 5 deg F, and took it to the sauna to check it out... passed with flying colors.

I can read the display just fine, although many reviewers say they want it brighter... Its easy to see even in bright sunlight for me, and the night light is great at night.  This watch is VERY COOL.

UPDATE:  I had one issue.  One of the new band's attachment screws came loose during use, and fell out.  The screw that came with the original band isn't the exact right length for the accessory rubber band, so I contacted Suunto (yes, Finland) through their website, and requested a new set of screws.  They sent them, and I just received them yesterday.  It took about 5 weeks, which they informed me up front.  During my wait, I used the original bands screws, but couldn't tighten all the way, as tight length is too short for the accessory band.  I have now used BLUE LOCTITE on all 4 band screws, and have not had any issue at all with loosening...Therefore, if you do get an accessory band, my recommendation is use Loctite.  AND, by the way, all the features of this watch work great...I use the barometer function with storm warning, and works very well.  Also, the compass is great.  However, this is one of those products that you need to understand how to use it to get the most benefit.  If you are willing to study a little on its use, it becomes addictive its so good.  I wear it 24-7.
summary: ... black rubber band makes this watch look so much better that the original band

reviewText:
For the price, this is a lovely strand of pearls for children.  The actual pearls are of so-so quality, often described as potato pears because of their more oval than round shape. I would like to say that for the price these are absolutely great!  My only complaints are 1) the clasp is a bit cheap. It has seven rhinestones in a flower shape, six around a center stone, all the same size. My daughter will love it, but I would have preferred a more traditional clasp. 2) on a nicer strand the silk string is covered with very fine coiled wire at the clasp to protect the high stress sites. I worry about the longevity of the actual clasp and the silk where it is attached to the clasp. Again, for the price these are fairly petty complaints.

reviewText: This watch is amazing. I remember the first time i saw an avenger like 6 years ago.. i immediately wanted one. Well i finally have made it a reality, i bought mine at ben bridge because i want warranty and paperwork, plus im assured it is new and not refurbished and only genuine parts. This watch is BIG im 6ft 195 and it is almost too big for me . Cream dial is classy as all hell and revokes its almost obnoxious size. The warranty "card" isn't a card at all like i got with my tag heuer rather a ipod sized lcd screen sporting object which is turned on and has all the info stored in it from purchase date through your lifetime of service. The chronometer certificate is also a amazing document im proud to know matches the movement in my watch.. i was considering other models. Superocean heritage cream dial green bezel diving bracelet (just wasn't as impressed with the overall stature though the bracelet is pure sex) and an iwc portofino cream on leather, also the gmt avenger which is alot more cream than this watch which officially has a "silver" dial in person its much less eggshell and more silver than the images from breitlings site and online. The gen 2 has a diff bracelet than gen1, wider center links. Also the inner bezel the is in direct contact with the sapphire crystal doesnt have those "slots" that gen1 has, i like this its a much cleaner rendition of a already iconic watch and this color dial is the classiest imo... if u are considering this... please do urself a favor and check an authorized dealer... ull pay 1500$ more...easily. but enjoy the satisfaction on genuine warranty and full documentation. I almost went for a white dial milgauss but decided it was too reserved for me....i love this watch and you will too

Excellent bag. Would highly recommend for sporting events. We keep this packed in the trunk, always ready for the various games we attend on a whim. It easily fits two light weight jackets (rolled up), a rolled up wind-proof blanket, 1 womens wallet, two 16oz water bottles, and two sunglass cases without any trouble. In the small zipper pocket, we keep our essentials: hand sanitizer, soft ear plugs, cash/cards/tickets, chapstick, and lotion. It zips across the top, but has small gaps on each end. I like this because I can easily reach in to grab my cell phone and slip it back in without trouble. Usually, I have my wallet accessible on one end, and my cell phone on the other end. I LOVE the cross body feature. It is adjustable, so it can easily fit both me and my husband (who is much taller and larger than myself). The size has never been an issue at any of the stadiums I have been to around the county (I noticed some commenters thought it may be too big).
Overall, I have found this to be the perfect bag for my game-day experience and would highly recommend it.

I suggested they label the measure unit because in the US, inches are mostly used for clothing and by not labeling it, it is not obvious to some (it was in centimeters). The seller took my suggestion and did just that immediately. The seller provides excellent customer service. He will email to make sure if you received the item.
